cast.text:
A potential simplification

*For users*
Farcaster - social networking app you can download in the app store

It's has a lot of cryptonative and crypto curious people. A lot of people building new stuff. There's a feed, messaging, an integrated wallet and mini-apps.

*For developers*

It's built on an open, permissionless decentralized system that any developer can access. 

And if you build a mini-app for Farcaster, other apps with lots of users (i.e. crypto wallets) can easily showcase your app in their app—massively increasing your distribution with no additional work from you. 

Ship once, be everywhere.

text:
The tokenomics may be interesting to some. I've got a memecoin, an NFT book, and a DAO governance token I think I want to combine. The NFT can be traded primarily for ETH on Alexandria's site, and that makes sense because that's the place to read that book. 

The DAO governance token is useful and interesting as a liquidity pair against $NSI because I have a bunch of both tokens and people will be able to trade $PAGE/$NSI for 1% on Uniswap once some $NSI is minted for $ETH. It adds a bit of play and flexibility and I'm thinking this way because I think it can be a scalable future for $PAGE and a good way to provide value at the ecosystem level (by locking $ETH), at the community level (by locking $PAGE), and at the user/author level (by locking $NSI, or perhaps just holding some).

https://epicdylan.com

text:
Hey Farcaster, I wrote a treatment up for a little film I like to call Zombienado. It’s a cartel/police thriller film with a serious zombie problem, lots of explosions, and enough pop culture tropes to make it a hit on the “B” film scene even without a star-studded cast. Or we could take it to Hollywood, raise a ton of money, and try to go the blockbuster route for it. 

I have no idea what to do, haven’t ever done anything film-related before, but I do feel some conviction in the silliness of the concept and the way it makes people laugh when I tell them about it. 

What should I do next? 

I could:

1. Write a book that thoroughly fleshes out the concept as I see it
2. Go straight to script and talk to producers about it
3. ??? (what have I not thought of? I’m using AI quite a bit in this project so I can iterate quickly but am ultimately still the one responsible for delivering quality here)

Hey! I'm a cofounder of the PageDAO [ https://pagedao.org ] also: PhD student in neuroscience. 

https://epicdylan.com

text: Alexandria Labs pushing Web3 publishing forward!! 🔥🥳🫡

cast.text:
This week I built: /alexandria's NFT ebook release of the Konrath Dark Thriller Collective with author J.A. Konrath, who’s sold a few million books worldwide. It’s a retrospective of his thrillers, plus brand new afterwords to each one that basically sum up to his autobiography, and a new exclusive novella. 16 novels, hundreds of unique covers, original music. The compendium ebook is 1.7 million words long!

We made this release, which included ebook download, on February 26, the same day Amazon stopped allowing Kindle ebook download.

So far we’ve gotten great feedback from Joe’s fans who were not into web3 at ALL, and now so many of them are saying they totally get why NFT books and true decentralized ebook ownership is important. This is mass onboarding!!

So grateful to  for such smooth, fast transactions, with low gas that makes it possible for us to offer these ebooks at prices comparable to web2 ebooks. This is how we onboard and it’s really working!

text: Change km to mi and this is about how I think and run 😅🤝

cast.text:
i wouldn’t have thought 2 months ago that I would be running 10k for a training session

but here we are. the target was 5:30/km, and as soon as i started i got the takeaway for today:

better to start slower and get used to the pace as the session progresses

i started too fast. i had also calculated the amount of seconds needed for 250m, and soon i discovered that it was better to get up with the pace with 100m intervals. 33 seconds each. that was way more helpful to find the pace

and then after getting it i started aiming for 66 seconds every 200m. that felt like it clicked

it’s amazing how it works once you catch up the pace. this is my first time running at this one. good session
